                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Mediocre.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black; red.</seg>
                        <date>Mid-18th – mid-19th century (?)</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; the name of the donor; the initial two
                           lines of Text I-1 and subsections of Text I-2; the word ʾǝsaggǝd “I
                           worship” in Text I-1; elements of the punctuation signs; elements of the
                           Ethiopic numerals.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Omitted letters inserted interlineally, possibly in the main hand: e.g., fols. 3rb, 4vb, 5rb, 7rb. - Omitted letters added at the beginning of the line: <locus target="#5ra">fol.  5ra</locus>, 5vb. - Erasure on <locus target="#5ra">fol.  5ra</locus>. - Scribbles in blue pen on <locus target="#4vb">fol.  4vb</locus> and in pencil on <locus target="#8va">fol.  8va</locus>.</item>
